PS52007D - Research Methods in Psychology 2022/3

Module Coordinator - Dr. Gordon Wright

This page offers an outline of the topics, content, and assignments for the semester. Note that this schedule will be updated as the semester progresses and the timeline of topics and assignments might be updated throughout the semester. boom.

Teaching Schedule 2022-23
Week Date Lectures Labs Prelude Slides Lab Extras Notes
Winter Term
1 3 Oct 2022 Module overview and what is Science? Welcome to the Lab - onboarding and topic brainwalking
2 10 Oct 2022 Asking good questions and gathering evidence The research process , time management & teamwork
3 17 Oct 2022 Being critical and evaluating the work of others Literature search, review, management & the Critical Proposal
4 24 Oct 2022 There is no 'I' in Psychology, or 'me'! MeSearch, Research & Inclusivity Experimental variables, design and notation
5 31 Oct 2022 The Open Science movement in Psychology Critical Proposal support and Power Calculations
7 Nov 2022 READING WEEK
6 14 Nov 2022 Operationalisation of variables and bringing concepts to life Online and offline data collection
7 21 Nov 2022 How do we measure or assess psychological concepts and constructs? Task development and Ethics applications
8 28 Nov 2022 Developing and validating a psychological measure of 'X' Task development and Ethics workshop [Peer Review]
9 5 Dec 2022 Communicating science: Lessons from legends Recruitment and thinking ahead to your Year 3 Dissertation
10 12 Dec 2022 Introducing the wonders of Qualitative research Pre-registration, Open Methods and Open Data
Winter Break
Spring Term
11 16 Jan 2023 Qualitative research in application Data collection | Beginning writing up
12 23 Jan 2023 Blending the Qs - Mixed Methods Data collection | Focus on the Method section
13 30 Jan 2023 Psychology that will get you paid Data collection | Analysis plan
14 6 Feb 2023 Year 3 Preview Session Data collection | Year One Showcase
15 13 Feb 2023 A deep dive on Inclusivity Data collection | Data screening, cleaning & pre-processing
20 Feb 2023 READING WEEK
16 27 Feb 2023 "No about me, without me!" Participatory research Analysis | The 3 flavours of ANOVA and post-hoc tests
17 6 Mar 2023 What questions is Psychology missing? Analysis |& Focus on Results, figures and tables
18 13 Mar 2023 So what is 'MyPsychology' Writing up | Focus on the Introduction & APA style
19 20 Mar 2023 A new 'People Science'? Writing up | Interpreting and discussing your results
20 27 Mar 2023 Roundup, reflection and retrospective Writing up | Open Data, Materials and final edits
SPRING BREAK
